-- Dish Bonds Decline After $25.5 Billion Offer to Acquire Sprint
-- B y   C h a r l e s   M e a d
-- 2013-04-15T13:22:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-15/dish-bonds-decline-after-25-5-billion-offer-to-acquire-sprint.html
Bonds of  Dish Network Corp. (DISH)  dropped
after Charlie Ergen’s satellite-TV company made an unsolicited
$25.5 billion offer for  Sprint Nextel Corp. (S)   Dish DBS Corp.’s $2 billion of 5.875 percent debt due July
2022 declined 1.9 cents to 100.75 cents on the dollar, yielding
5.77 percent at 9:07 a.m. in New York, according to Trace, the
bond-price reporting system of the Financial Industry Regulatory
Authority.  To contact the reporter on this story:
